{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012HPjy2hBC4drx43eEdtRPz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to patch the ingress-nginx controller ConfigMap to enable OpenTelemetry. For ingress-nginx v1.14.1, the OpenTelemetry configuration is done via ConfigMap keys:\n\n- `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` - enables OTel\n- `otlp-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"` - OTel collector host\n- `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"` - OTel collector port (gRPC)\n- `opentelemetry-trust-incoming-span: \"true\"` - trust incoming W3C trace context\n- `opentelemetry-sample-rate: \"1.0\"` - 100% sampling\n- `log-format-upstream` - custom log format with OTel variables\n\nI'll use kubectl patch to update the ConfigMap with these settings. The sampling rate key might vary between versions, so I need to verify whether it's `otel-sampler-ratio` or `opentelemetry-sample-rate` for this version.\n\nLooking at the ingress-nginx v1.x documentation for OpenTelemetry support, the configuration keys include `enable-opentelemetry`, `otlp-collector-host`, `otlp-collector-port`, `opentelemetry-trust-incoming-span`, and the sampler options like `otel-sampler` and `otel-sampler-ratio`. I'll go with `opentelemetry-sample-rate: \"1\"` for 100% sampling and configure the log format as a single-line string that includes the OpenTelemetry trace and span IDs, then patch the configmap with these settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2175,"cache_read_input_tokens":31868,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2175},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ae57d5e-78ff-4784-a8d6-437fec24ce0a","uuid":"627a5633-695c-4fae-96f7-7b19c31b9f1d","request_id":"req_011CcL9mW3B